race.comment: CAN'T CATCH ME (9) led them up first-up at this track and trip and was only caught late, missing by 0.2L. Loses Pike, but should be better for that effort and she draws slightly better this time around. Rates highly already, but with further improvement on the cards, she looks the one to beat. GOD'S CROSS (7) was slowly away and ended up at the rear, but closed off well over 1000m at Bunbury on debut. Drawn out again, but the rise to 1200m looks ideal and if he can jump on terms today, he can be right in the finish. EL ALAMEIN (6) disappointed when fresh at Ascot and has trialled twice since that effort 36 days ago. Should be much fitter now and the claim of Martinan means he'll carry no weight. Expecting an improved effort today. YOUANMI (8) was sound on debut and that should lay the platform for him to build on here. DESERT WAVES (3) is here off a long break but his recent trial was solid. Worth thought.
